Project Structure Created:
1. Build Configuration
pom.xml: Maven project configuration with all necessary dependencies:
Jira REST Java Client for API integration
Apache POI for Excel file handling
Jackson for JSON processing
SLF4J for logging
JUnit 5 for testing
2. Core Java Modules
JiraIntegration.java: Handles Jira API authentication and operations

authenticate(): Connects to Jira
createTestCase(): Creates test cases in Jira
updateTestExecution(): Updates test execution results
fetchTestCases(): Retrieves test cases from Jira
ExcelTestCaseReader.java: Reads test cases from Excel files

readTestCases(): Parses Excel data
getFieldMapping(): Maps Excel columns to Jira fields
TestCaseSynchronizer.java: Orchestrates synchronization

syncTestCases(): Syncs from Excel to Jira
syncTestResults(): Syncs test results back
Main.java: Application entry point with workflow orchestration

3. Testing Framework
JiraIntegrationTest.java: Unit tests for Jira operations
ExcelTestCaseReaderTest.java: Tests for Excel parsing
TestCaseSynchronizerTest.java: Integration tests
4. Configuration & Documentation
application.properties: Configuration file for Jira credentials and settings
README.md: Comprehensive documentation with setup instructions, usage examples, and troubleshooting
Key Features:
✅ Automated synchronization between Excel and Jira
✅ Test case management and tracking
✅ Execution result updates
✅ Comprehensive logging
✅ Unit test coverage
✅ Maven build system
✅ Proper error handling

The project is now ready for development and testing. You can clone the repository and run mvn clean install to build the project!
